  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A subset of 120 diabetic patients underwent dilated examination and smartphone
      ophthalmoscopy. The smartphone was equipped with a compact add-on that filtered and delivered
      the smartphone's LED light coaxially to the camera, allowing a clear and convenient view of
      the retina.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
